# Task: Create Leaderboard with Persistent High Scores

You are adding a persistent leaderboard system with a game-over state to a browser-based Three.js ball game.

## Codebase

Pure static HTML+JS served by nginx. No npm, no build step.
- `index.html` — Main page with Three.js importmap and overlay UI
- `js/main.js` — Game loop, state management, wires tracker to physics to renderer
- `js/tracker.js` — MediaPipe FaceLandmarker head tilt detection (DO NOT MODIFY)
- `js/physics.js` — Ball physics (lateral movement, forward speed, falling, collision detection)
- `js/renderer.js` — Three.js scene (track, ball, camera, lighting, obstacles, coins)
- `Dockerfile` + `nginx.conf` — Docker build serving on port 8080

## Libraries
- Three.js v0.183.2 (CDN via importmap): all 3D rendering
- No new dependencies allowed
- Uses standard browser APIs: localStorage, DOM manipulation

## Current State Machine

`main.js` has states: `loading | permission | playing | falling`

Current reset flow (lines 121-138 of main.js):
```js
if (result.needsReset && state === 'falling') {
  if (!resetTimer) {
    resetTimer = setTimeout(() => {
      regenerateLevel();
      const config = getTrackConfig();
      config.obstacles = getObstacles();
      config.coins = getCoins();
      initPhysics(config);
      resetTilt();
      resetBallRotation();
      updateScore(0);
      updateBallPosition(0, config.trackHeight / 2 + config.ballRadius, config.ballStartZ);
